attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, Motorola m68k, 68020, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, missing section headers at jd

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a malicious IoT botnet, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt, compiled for the RISC-V (rv32gc) architecture. It exhibits classic botnet behavior including process scanning and termination of common system services (sshd, systemd-journald, etc.) via /proc iteration, the use of a mutex-like lock file at '/tmp/.bot_lock', and hardcoded HTTP request templates (GET, POST, HEAD) for DDoS attacks. The binary also utilizes a static 52-character hex key ('242c888359ab5dd13c9947a7f07dee87f6c90ec3b01f1492cca') across multiple subroutines, indicating string obfuscation or a custom communication protocol.
